                        "hint": "Use str() to convert to string",
                        "correctFeedback": "Perfect! You converted the number to a string.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Use str() to convert to string",
                        "explanation": "Use str() to convert any value to a string."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_convert_to_integer",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "code_fill",
                    "content": "Convert the string `\"30\"` to an integer.",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "lines": [
                            {
                                "code": "text = \"30\"",
                                "indent": 0
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "number = {1}(text)",
                                "indent": 0,
                                "blank": "1"
                            }
                        ],
                        "options": [
                            "int",
                            "integer"
                        ],
                        "solutions": {
                            "1": "int"
                        },
                        "hint": "Use int() to convert to integer",
                        "correctFeedback": "Great! You converted the string to an integer.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Use int() to convert to integer",
                        "explanation": "Use int() to convert strings or floats to integers."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_convert_to_float",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "code_fill",
                    "content": "Convert the string `\"15.5\"` to a float.",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "lines": [
                            {
                                "code": "text = \"15.5\"",
                                "indent": 0
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "decimal = float({1})",
                                "indent": 0,
                                "blank": "1"
                            }
                        ],
                        "options": [
                            "text"
                        ],
                        "solutions": {
                            "1": "text"
                        },
                        "hint": "Use float() to convert to float",
                        "correctFeedback": "Excellent! You converted the string to a float.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Use float() to convert to float",
                        "explanation": "Use float() to convert strings or integers to floats."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "conversion_limitations",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "One thing to note is that you can only convert strings that contain **valid numbers** to integers or floats."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "# Correct\nnumber = int(\"25\")\n\n# Incorrect\nnumber = int(\"hello\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_whats_wrong_conversion",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "What's wrong with this type conversion?"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "text = \"hello\"\nnumber = int(text)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "mcq",
                    "content": "",
                    "properties": {
                        "question": "",
                        "options": [
                            "The string is too long",
                            "The string is not numerical"
                        ],
                        "correctAnswerIndex": 1,
                        "correctFeedback": "Correct! You can't convert text to a number.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "You can only convert strings that contain numbers.",
                        "explanation": "int() only works with strings that contain valid numbers."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_convert_and_add",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Let's say we need to add 50 to the `score_string`."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code_fill",
                    "content": "We will have to first convert the `score_string` to an integer.",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "lines": [
                            {
                                "code": "score_string = \"100\"",
                                "indent": 0
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "score = {1}(score_string)",
                                "indent": 0,
                                "blank": "1"
                            }
                        ],
                        "options": [
                            "int",
                            "number"
                        ],
                        "solutions": {
                            "1": "int"
                        },
                        "hint": "Use int() to convert the string to a number",
                        "correctFeedback": "Great! You converted the string to an integer for calculation.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Use int() to convert the string to a number",
                        "explanation": "Convert strings to numbers before doing calculations."
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_convert_and_add",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "code_fill",
                    "content": "Now we can safely add 50 to the `score`.",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "lines": [
                            {
                                "code": "score_string = \"100\"",
                                "indent": 0
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "score = int(score_string)",
                                "indent": 0
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "result = {1} + 50",
                                "indent": 0,
                                "blank": "1"
                            },
                            {
                                "code": "print(result)",
                                "indent": 0
                            }
                        ],
                        "options": [
                            "score_string",
                            "score"
                        ],
                        "solutions": {
                            "1": "score"
                        },
                        "hint": "Use the score variable for calculation",
                        "correctFeedback": "Great! You converted the string to an integer for calculation.",
                        "incorrectFeedback": "Use the score variable for calculation",
                        "explanation": "Convert strings to numbers before doing calculations.",
                        "output": "150"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
